14/08/2009
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Tourism Minister Damir Bajs expressed regret and condemned on Thursday (August 13th) an incident involving Italian tourists who were insulted and beaten in Katina, on the Kornati Islands. The five tourists had quarrelled with a local restaurant owner over their bill. Bajs stressed that such treatment will not be tolerated. The incident came a week after a similar assault involving Oscar-winning Czech film director Jiri Menzel in the town of Dubrovnik. Menzel was attacked by the owner and employees of a local restaurant. (HRT, HINA, Croatian times - 13/08/09)
